{
  "analysis": "The current /app/mystery.c is an incorrect guessed raytracer, verified wrong by md5 (a36bc6586fa014f9e174053d77d88f53 vs required e866fa2c851f4a9da736b4ed3ba3912e). The required behavior is known: print fixed stdout messages and write image.ppm byte-for-byte identical to /tmp/original.ppm. We have helper disassembly files and extracted constants, but rodata string extraction returned empty because it used virtual addresses without mapping to file offsets. The next concrete step is to dump the actual .rodata bytes around file offset 0x80000 and print the beginning of sphere_intersect in small chunks. This will provide exact format strings and intersection logic needed for reconstruction. I will not write another guessed implementation until verification passes.",
  "plan": "Dump .rodata bytes from file offset 0x80000-0x80200 as ASCII to find exact format strings and messages. Then print sphere_intersect lines 1-60 and 61-120. Also print main disassembly lines 81-160 in a small chunk. This avoids truncation and provides exact algorithm details for reconstruction. I will not finalize a candidate yet.",
